\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. A. tenorii} C. Presl in J. & C. Presl,{\i  Del. Prag.} 79 (1822). Rhizomatous perennial, acaulescent or with stem up to 5 cm; glabrous or sparsely hairy. Leaves 18-50 × 10-20 mm, oblong-obovate or spathulate, crenate-dentate. Bracts lanceolate, at least the upper shorter than the flowers. Calyx 5-6 mm, the teeth slightly longer than the tube. Corolla 16-25 mm, bright blue; tube exceeding calyx; upper lip entire or with 2 short teeth. Stamens exserted; filaments usually hairy. •{\i  Mountains of C. & S. Italy and Sicilia.} It Si.
\par

