\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. A. salicifolia} (L.) Schreber,{\i  Pl. Vert. Unilab.} 26 (1773). Perennial; stem 20-30 cm, woody at base, lanate-villous. Lower leaves 25-60 × 10-22 mm, oblong-elliptical or lanceolate, entire or dentate; cauline leaves cuneate at base. Bracts similar to the leaves, exceeding the flowers. Flowers 2 at each node. Calyx 6-10(-11) mm, the teeth shorter than the tube. Corolla 18-25(-28) mm, yellow; tube slightly exceeding calyx; upper lip with 2 short lobes. Stamens exserted; filaments hairy.{\i  S.E. Europe, from Turkey-in-Europe to Krym.} Bu Rm Rs (K) Tu.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp.{\b  salicifolia}: Cauline hairs 0·2-1 mm, appressed to semipatent. Calyx (7-)8-11 mm. {\i Krym}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b bassarabica}(Savul. & Zahar.) P. W. Ball, {\i Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc.}{\b  65}: 258 (1972) ({\i A. oblongata} Bieb. subsp.{\i  bassarabica} Savul. & Zahar.): Cauline hairs dimorphic, some c. 0·2 mm, crispate, the rest 1-1·5 mm, straight, patent. Calyx 6-10 mm. {\i From E. Romania to Turkey-in-Europe}.
